                <summary>The January Term of the County Court met, J. M. McCue presiding. J. C.
                    Wheat and J. W. Baldwin renewed their bonds as Notaries Public. The estates of
                    A. D. Chandler and Jacob Dull were entrusted to Samuel Paul for administration.
                    Petitions were received from John Churchman and Chesley Kinney for changes of
                    public roads. David Kerr, Simeon Koiner, and James W. Patterson were appointed
                    road surveyors. Chesley Kenny's hotel license was transferred to J. A.
                    Hefelfinger. Jack and Rebecca Walker, "colored," and Ella Zambro, white, were
                    ordered to be bound out. R. G. Bickle and H. H. Peck were appointed to repair
                    the Jail floor and purchase coal for the furnace. Thomas W. Shelton and James W.
                    Cochran were exempted from paying erroneous taxes.</summary>
                <note/>
